<section class="guide">
  <h1>3. Connect Cloudflare Pages</h1>
  <p class="lead">Set up hosting with automatic deployments on every git push.</p>

  <h2>Why Cloudflare Pages?</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Auto-deploy:</strong> Push to GitHub and your site updates automatically</li>
    <li><strong>Free unlimited sites:</strong> No per-site costs, unlimited bandwidth</li>
    <li><strong>Free SSL:</strong> HTTPS certificates auto-provisioned</li>
    <li><strong>Global CDN:</strong> Fast load times worldwide via Cloudflare's edge network</li>
    <li><strong>Built-in Web Analytics:</strong> Traffic data per domain, no snippet needed</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Prerequisites</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>A Cloudflare account (free)</li>
    <li>GitHub OAuth connected in Cloudflare dashboard (Pages &gt; Connect to Git)</li>
    <li>A scoped Cloudflare API token with <code>Cloudflare Pages:Edit</code> and <code>Zone:DNS:Edit</code> permissions</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>Create a Pages Project</h2>

  <h3>Option A: Let Your Assistant Do It (Recommended)</h3>
  <p>Ensure the <code>CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN</code> is set as a Railway env var with <code>EXTRA_ENV_KEYS=CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN</code>.</p>

  <p>Then tell your assistant:</p>
  <blockquote>"Create a Cloudflare Pages project for my repo."</blockquote>

  <p>The assistant will call the Cloudflare API to create a Pages project linked to your GitHub repo, with build command <code>npm run build</code> and output directory <code>_site</code>.</p>

  <h3>Option B: Use the Cloudflare Dashboard</h3>
  <ol>
    <li>Go to Cloudflare dashboard &gt; Pages</li>
    <li>Click "Create a project" &gt; "Connect to Git"</li>
    <li>Select your GitHub repository</li>
    <li>Set build command: <code>npm run build</code></li>
    <li>Set output directory: <code>_site</code></li>
    <li>Deploy!</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>Verify Deployment</h2>
  <p>After setup, your site will be available at:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Pages URL:</strong> Something like <code>https://project-slug.pages.dev</code></li>
  </ul>

  <p>Visit the URL to confirm your site is live! Build logs are available in the Cloudflare dashboard.</p>

